text: The 1930 Kentucky Wildcats football team was an American football team that represented the University of Kentucky in the Southern Conference during the 1930 college football season. In their fourth season under head coach Harry Gamage, the Wildcats compiled a 5–3 record (4–3 against conference opponents), tied for 11th place in the conference, and outscored opponents by a total of 207 to 55. The team played its home games at McLean Stadium in Lexington, Kentucky. ==Schedule== ==References== Kentucky Category:Kentucky Wildcats football seasons Kentucky Wildcats football
